Legal Calculus 4.5 — Enhanced Modules — Module 44
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 44

Findings-to-Exhibit Matrix — Proof for Every Element

⚖️ Core Message

Tie each required finding to exact pages of your exhibits.
📖 Lesson Content

1. Matrix Columns: Element/Factor • Exhibit • Page/Pin • Short Proof Phrase.
2. Avoid 'see generally'; point to lines/paragraphs.
3. File the matrix with PI/SJ motions and after hearings if allowed.
4. Use the matrix to draft your proposed findings quickly.
📝 Assignment

Draft a 12‑cell matrix mapping elements to exhibit pages with short proof phrases.
✅ Model Response

MATRIX (excerpt)

Irreparable Harm | Ex. D | p.2 | 'Delivery delay blocks review'

 

💡 Reflection Summary

The best finding is the one you already mapped.
🎨 Visual Concept

A checklist where each factor points to a page number.
